properties.headline: Special Weather Statement issued January 10 at 4:17AM CST by NWS Green Bay WI
properties.description:
Any remaining water on area roadways and sidewalks may refreeze
this morning across much of the area. This will lead to slippery
spots on untreated surfaces, which may impact the morning commute.

Light to moderate snow is expected to develop this evening and
then linger through much of tonight. Snowfall totals are generally
expected to be in the 1 to 3 inch range across the area, with the
greatest totals expected from the Fox Valley to the lakeshore. In
addition, winds may gust as high as 30 mph late tonight, which
will likely lead to reduced visibilities at times.

Please allow extra time to reach your destination if traveling
this morning or tonight and be alert for rapidly changing road
conditions due to black ice or snow covered roads.

NWSheadline: SLIPPERY CONDITIONS POSSIBLE THIS MORNING AND LIGHT TO MODERATE SNOW AND BLOWING SNOW EXPECTED TONIGHT
